Edward Banks, publisher
editor of the Arizona Tribune,
delivered the major address at
a meeting of the Young Republic
cans Club at the University of
Southern California, Los Angeles
on Wednesday, May 20.


He appeared as guest speaker
also at Republican meetings
held Thursday and Friday at
UCLA and Los Angeles City Col
lege.


MIR. Banks will address the
monthly meeting of the 2lst Con-
gressional District Republican
Club, also.


His topics are "a Converse
tive's View and San Arizonan
Looks at G oldwater.''

10 years after the Supreme Court
school integration ruling. He con-
tinued the protest was against
segregation which was still prac-
ticed in the South and also de
facto segregation.

test rally was held at Eastlake

ATLANTA = The Council of
Federate Organizations, civil
rights group. is seeking 1000
volunteers in colleges for duty in
Mississippi this summer.


Students are asked to come for
three weeks and live with Negro
families. They are asked to have
at least $3.50 for expenses and
$4OO for bail bond. If needed.


These students will spearhead
a voter registration project and
teach in freedom schools in Mis-
sissippi.

ject."
